[1
Date: Sunday 29 June 1997
From: Chuck Haas <haascn@post.drexel.edu>
The median infectious dose (ID50) for _Shigella_ species that we have
examined appears to be around 1000 organisms, and the dose-response curve is
consistent with the beta-poisson model that we have developed. There appear
to have been outbreaks in which the average dose ingested was on the order of
10 organisms. See the following reference for details on this model (which I
know is being looked at as a possible template for VTEC):
"Prevalence of Shigellosis in the U.S.: Consistency with Dose-Response
Information", C. Crockett, C.N. Haas, A. Fazil, J.B. Rose, and C.P. Gerba,
International Journal of Food Microbiology, 30(1-2):87-100 (1996).
Charles N. Haas <haascn@dunx1.ocs.drexel.edu>
Betz Professor of Environmental Engineering
Drexel University
Philadelphia PA 19104
owner: ENVENG-L
http://httpsrv.ocs.drexel.edu/faculty/haascn
